text.text: The NUS Blood Donation Drive is back!

text: Don’t miss out on this opportunity to donate blood🩸! Each blood donation has the potential to save 3 lives ❤️❤️❤️

text.text:
Date: 6 & 7 February 2024
Time: 10am to 4pm
Location: NUS University Sports Centre MPSH2

text:
When else can you save lives while enjoying a nice nap and some snacks?

We’ve prepared a special goodie bag as a token of appreciation for our donors, including vouchers from ClearVision, Kimage, I’m Kim Korean BBQ, and more!

Sign up now to donate blood! ⏰
We are also recruiting volunteers to help us out with guiding donors, managing crowds, and setting up & clearing the venue!
Sign up now! ➡️

For any queries, please contact us through Telegram:
Project Director -
Vice Project Director -

We hope to see you there! 😄

Donate Blood, Save Lives!🩸

messages.text:
HELLO EVERYONE! NEW SEM NEW GROUP!! 

Tired of missing announcements for house events?🥺 Missed some supper open jios last sem that left you going to sleep hungry?😩 Fret not! 

Welcome back to sem 2! We have decided that it will be good to create a new chat with different channels so that announcements won't be missed and open jios will always be seen! So here's some guidelines for the new topics :)) 

CHITCHAT 💬
- general chat! Open jios, chit chats and everything else under the sun can be sent here! 

📣 ANNOUNCEMENTS
- House events details, and other comms that might need to do publicity can be sent via this channels

🎙ROCHELPLINE
- need help to come up cos you forgot your card? A screwdriver or some tape? This is your channel to turn to. Any calls for help from fellow Rockers can be sent here! 

🧽 LAUNDRY UPDATES
"D1 done!" "W2 done!!" 

Try to stick to what each of the topics are for and not send texts that may not belong in there🙆🏻‍♂! 

Thanks for reading till this point and happy sem 2☺️

text:
Listen up!! CAPTSLAM Townsquare is welcoming YOU to join and TAKE CHARGE as PD/VPD of the programme for AY24/25! 🤗💕🌳🤠

CAPT Student Leader Action Mentorship (SLAM) Townsquare is a value-based mentorship programme in Semester 1 that partners with students from New Town Secondary School (NTSS) to encourage their growth as individuals who are grounded in their core values. CAPTSLAM Townsquare concludes with an overseas trip to Chiang Mai at the end of Semester 1 during the Winter Break.

As the PD/VPD, you will be involved in directing the programme's vision and leading the planning and execution of the mentorship activities both locally and in Chiang Mai. It will truly be an enriching and enjoyable journey! 

If you have any queries, feel free to reach out to any of the current PDs via Telegram:
Beatrice (PD)
/ Ferdows (VPD)
/ Victoria (VPD)
Application closes on
. Sign up

messages.text:
Dear Residents

With regard to the recent cases of expired juice cartons at the Grab&Go station, an investigation by NUS Dining Services has been conducted on the CAPT/RC4 DH caterer.

Cause:
The supplier has mixed in some expired ones into the batches of juice they deliver to the caterers. Notably, only the Mango juice has expired cartons. The caterer has not kept any expired juices from last semester.

Current Actions:
1. Random spotchecks by caterer on deliveries by supplier.
- not logistically possible to check every single packet of juice
2. Checks by waiting staff.
- waiting staff are mostly elderly and myopic and sometimes misreads the dates on the packets

Future Actions:
1. SFA has been notified of the food safety breach
2. NUS Dining Services will seek compensation from the caterers as per their contract.
3. Mango juice will be stopped and changed to a different type of juice.
4. Cooperation of residents sought to keep an eye out for expired juices and return them to the waiting staff.

If you notice any future incidences of food safety lapses (e.g. expired food, uncooked food), please do the following:
1. Take a picture
2. Let your RA know
3. Let the catering managers know (their picture will be put up soon, but they generally dress much better than the average person)
4. Return the food and get a replacement

Cheers!

for you to sign up as PD/VPD of CAPTSLAM Townsquare and TAKE CHARGE of the programme in AY24/25! 🤗💕🌳🤠

CAPT Student Leader Action Mentorship (SLAM) Townsquare is a value-based mentorship programme in Semester 1 that partners with students from New Town Secondary School (NTSS) to encourage their growth as individuals who are grounded in their core values. CAPTSLAM Townsquare concludes with an overseas trip to Chiang Mai at the end of Semester 1 during the Winter Break.

As the PD/VPD, you will be involved in directing the programme's vision and leading the planning and execution of the mentorship activities both locally and in Chiang Mai. It will truly be an enriching and enjoyable journey! 

If you have any queries, feel free to reach out to any of the current PDs via Telegram:

text: Dear CAPTains, our CAPT fellows are looking for a good writer or two and understand CE in CAPT. It is paid work @ $20 per hour through the NSWS scheme. Timeline and pay are open for discussion! The details are as follows:

1.⁠ ⁠CE Programme Training and Reflection Toolkit:
Currently, different CE committees conduct training and reflection sessions with their materials. This project aims to create a consolidated toolkit, including training and reflection materials, that all CE programmes in CAPT can use. The following steps should be taken:
•⁠  ⁠Review all the training and reflection materials from the different CE programmes in CAPT.
•⁠  ⁠Conduct an informal survey with current student participants to evaluate the usefulness of the training and reflection materials.
•⁠  ⁠Conduct a survey with student leaders and participants to identify any critical or necessary training materials that need to be included.
•⁠  ⁠(If time permits) Review training materials from the Office of Student Affairs and other entities.
•⁠  ⁠Take any other necessary steps to complete the project.
 
Note: We are looking for two student assistants for this project.

: The desired outcome is to produce a tool kit that includes PowerPoint slides for standardised CE training and reflections for all CAPTains and a Word document for the training and reflection materials and provides addendum training and reflection for individual CE committees where necessary.

Do drop me a message if you are interested and/or have any questions! You can sign up with a friend of course! But first come first serve🤝️️️️️️  

On behalf of our CAPT fellows, 
Rowena

text.text: Q: What is TR2 training for? Should I attend?

text:
• You should attend TR training to familiarise yourself with the equipment in the TRs, how to use them properly, as well as learn about the various rules to take note of, especially if you intend to book or use the TRs anytime during AY23/24. 
• At least 1 TR trained personnel has to be

Get ready for a fun and meaningful speed dating experience! 💑 Join us for 4-minute conversations with potential matches, all packed into an hour of mingling and connection-building.

, hosted by the 12th Social Innovation (SI) Wing with our partners, the Meownistry of Meow (MOM), Foreword Coffee and CAPT coffee! 🐱☕️
  
In recent years, a surge in cat abandonments has been observed, stemming from impulsive pet purchases during the COVID-19 lockdown. Hence, our mission: promote adoption, ease shelter burden.

text:
Hey CAPTains! ✨

Didn’t manage to get a ticket for Arts Showcase 2024? No worries! 🌟 ClubSocs, with the fantastic support of our house heads, is excited to offer you a cozy alternative. Join us in your house lounge to watch the performances live!

📅

26 February 2024 (Monday)
⏰

8pm - 10pm
🏠
L4 Lounge & YouTube Live -

Don't miss out on this night bringing you a trip down memory lane 🤩 So, gather your friends, make yourselves comfortable, and be part of the show together! A huge shoutout to our house heads for making this possible! 🙌

Set your reminders, and let’s enjoy the night together. 🌙

See you at the lounge! 🎶
— 12th ClubSocs

Hi guys, as the open house is tmr, here is a gentle reminder to help:

1. Keep your area clean
2. Erase any inappropriate stuff on your door
3. Keep your shoes/slides in your room as there will be alot of ppl walking around and to prevent them from tripping over your shoes
4. Keep your doors lock for those not displaying your room to the public
5. For those displaying your room, keep all valuables hidden (ie keep laptop in the closet)

Thank you for your help!!

CAPTSLAM Queensway 👑 will be heading to Cambodia 🇰🇭 in early July this year to engage with the community of children and youths 👧👦 in Siem Reap. This donation drive will help to provide them with the supplies they need in their educational journey ✏️! 

Date 🗓:

, Monday (11/3) - Friday (15/3) 
Time ⏰ :
Location ‼️:

Items you can donate 🙇🏻‍♀️: 
 1. Secondhand clothes 👚 
 2. Socks 🧦 
 3. Stationaries 📏✏️
 4. Notebooks 📓
 5. Textbooks & Workbooks (Kindergarten/Primary) 📕
 6. School Shoes 👟 
 7. School Bags 🎒

💭 We hope the children can get the best quality of supplies we can give! Please ensure that your clothes/socks have no holes or explicit language ❌🤬 on them, and it would be amazing if the school supplies are in good condition (e.g. blank workbooks) 🤩! 

If you have any enquiries, do contact Xuan Zi (
), Magdalene (
), or Si Ying (

text:
Dear CAPTains, 

Please refer to the image for the schedule of the CSC Elections Dialogue Sessions. The dialogue session will be held physically at the Flying Seed on
, and

, subject to the maximum capacity of the venue.

In light of limited capacity available, the dialogue sessions will also be live streamed via Zoom and the recordings will be uploaded onto Canvas after the sessions. More instructions as well as the Zoom link will be provided before the actual dialogue. 

Additionally, the forum has also been opened on the Canvas page ‘CAPT001’ and you are welcome to post questions in the respective forums for the candidates until 2300hrs on 13 Mar (Wed). Candidates will be given till 2359hrs on 13 Mar (Wed) to respond to any last questions before the end of the campaigning period.

Any questions about the elections process should be directed to the Elections Committee.

Best regards,
13th CSC Elections Committee

text: Dear CAPTains,

As a College, it is important that we acknowledge the contribution of individuals who, through their commitment and dedication, have enriched community life in its broadest sense. 

The CAPT Awards are meant to recognize CAPTains who have been exceptional in demonstrating the College values of integrity, audacity, compassion and teachability (I-ACT), in any aspect of College life. This includes:

- Leadership and service
- Learning and intellectual growth
- Sports
- Arts and culture
- Community engagement            

All CAPTains are invited and encouraged to make one or more nominations for the various categories, and the awardees will be announced at the

There is no fixed number of awards; we hope to recognize as many deserving individuals as possible. Amongst the awardees under the College Award category, one or more outstanding individuals may also receive the CAPTain of the Year Award.

So, if you feel that a fellow CAPTain has inspired you and has gone the extra mile for the good of the College, help us recognize these individuals and celebrate their contributions as a community.

The nomination period

text.text: starts today and will end on 25 March, 2359hrs.

text: We look forward to receiving your

.

Best regards,
College of Alice & Peter Tan

Hi all, thank you for your support during the HH Dialogue Session. With this, we have now officially opened the voting period. Please note that as we are in the cooling-off period, campaigning is strictly prohibited.

The voting form can be accessed via this

. Rest assured that your data and decision will remain confidential and only RAs will have access to the data collected.

Voting method: this is a vote of confidence, meaning you can vote for one, both, or none of the candidate(s).

1. The minimum number of vote required is 60.
2. Candidates must have more than 66% confidence votes to be elected.
3. If none or only one candidate has more than 66% votes, we will be opening Round 2 sometime in Week 9.

Please note that the election period begins on Saturday (16 March) 0900 and ends on Monday (18 March) 2359. No extension will be given after the form has closed. Results will be released on Tuesday.

If you have any questions, please feel free to reach out to the RAs

. Thank you!

- With 💙, Roc RAs

📚

Good day CAPTains!

CAPT Kamal will be spending 2 weeks in Bangalore, India, in May this year 🇮🇳

We will be having a donation drive to collect supplies and items to donate to the underpriviledged youths at our overseas community partner, Dream School Foundation 🏫

📅 
1. Week 9 Mon (18 Mar) 8-10pm 
2. Week 10 Mon (25 Mar) 8-10pm 
3. Week 11 Mon (1 Apr) 8-10pm 
4. Week 11 Thu (4 Apr) 8-10pm 
*all dates @ 12 Lounge 

Items you can donate:☺️

1. Lab coats 
2. Toy microphones
3. Toy cameras
4. Headbands (photobooth props, cute cartoons)
5. Costumes (aprons, chef hats)
6. Food & Kitchen props

1. Coloured/origami paper 
2. Drawing tools (coloured pencils, markers) 
3. Paints 
4. Clear folders 
5. Clipboards
6. Mini whiteboards

1. Traditional games (Chaptehs, Pick-up sticks, Country erasers, Five stones) 
2. Bracelet-making craft beads and strings 
3. Brain teasers/puzzles
4. Sporting goods 
5. Yoga mats 

If you have any of these items in good condition, please bring them to our donation booths during the various slots! Your donations will go a long way and make a positive difference to the youths! 🥰🥰

If you have any questions, feel free to PM ian (
) or laura (

messages.text:
Sure, let's add a bit of humor to celebrate Tze Kai's new role as Sports Director:

In the realm of CAPT, where sport is king,
Tze Kai steps up, ready to do his thing.
Sports Director now, with a grin so wide,
He’s plotting fun, with nowhere to hide.

“Yoga with goats, or dodgeball on skates?
Why not both?” he debates.
His plans are wild, his ideas are bold,
“Let’s play tag with blindfolds!”

From soccer with bubbles to racing in sacks,
Tze Kai’s the maestro of hilarious acts.
With a whistle and cap, and a mischievous smile,
He’s turning gym sessions into a comedy mile.

“Let’s swap the basketball for a balloon,
And play volleyball under the moon.
Why jog around, when we can hop on one foot?
Trust me, it’s fun, just follow my route!”

The athletes laugh, they can’t keep straight faces,
As Tze Kai leads them through his funny paces.
But beneath the jests and the playful fun,
His heart beats strong for victory won.

So here’s to Tze Kai, with his unique flair,
Making sports a hoot, beyond compare.
Though we may giggle, stumble, and fall,
We’ll say, “With Tze Kai, we’ve had a ball!”

Hey CAPTains, want to take a break from the stressful midterm period?😮‍💨Want to reconnect with nature and bond with friends at the same time? 🍃🍃 Green CAPTains has something just for you!

Come join us on our first-ever cycling trip in Pulau Ubin! 🚲 Re-experience the natural beauty of the island 🏝️🏝️ through a moderate cycling trail which will let you destress and have a memorable time with your peers as well! 🤗

Date: 23 Mar (Week 9 Sat)
Time: 7.45am - 1.15pm
Cost: $8 (inclusive of 1-way bus and 2-way bumboat rides)

*Do note that a moderate cycling experience is required for safety reasons

For more information, feel free to contact Nadya (
) or Bryan (
). Thank you and we hope to see you there!

Happy week 10!
Have a guitar you don't use anymore? Don't FRET😄 You can now DONATE them to the boys at Singapore Boys' Hostel by 🗓️

🔥

ACE Constellations aims to empower youths-at-risk through a guitar-teaching programme so that they may use music as a form of self-expression and emotional regulation. However, these boys do not have their own guitar... this donation drive will help to provide them with their very own guitar to practice and play whenever, wherever! Will this be the start of their singer-songwriter era? 🤔😎🤩

All types of guitars are welcomed, preferably in good condition! 🎸

If you are keen to give your guitars a new home, do contact Elijah (
) or Yien Ning (
) for the next step, by 25 April (Thursday)! Thank you for your donations❤️

Happy end of week 9 CAPTains!

CAPT Kamal will be spending 2 weeks in Bangalore, India, in May this year 🇮🇳

We will be having a donation drive to collect supplies and items to donate to the underpriviledged youths at our overseas community partner, Dream School Foundation 🏫

📅 
1. Week 9 Mon (18 Mar) 8-10pm ✅
2. Week 10 Mon (25 Mar) 6-8pm ⏳
3. Week 11 Mon (1 Apr) 6-8pm ⏳
4. Week 11 Thu (4 Apr) 6-8pm ⏳
*all dates @ CAPT Bermuda Triangle (outside DH)! 

Items you can donate:☺️
*Lists are not exhaustive

1. Lab coats 
2. Toy microphones
3. Toy cameras
4. Headbands (photobooth props, cute cartoons)
5. Costumes (aprons, chef hats)
6. Food & Kitchen props

1. Coloured/origami paper 
2. Drawing tools (coloured pencils, markers) 
3. Paints 
4. Clear folders 
5. Clipboards
6. Mini whiteboards

1. Traditional games (Chaptehs, Pick-up sticks, Country erasers, Five stones) 
2. Bracelet-making craft beads and strings 
3. Brain teasers/puzzles
4. Sporting goods 
5. Yoga mats 

If you have any of these items in good condition, please bring them to our donation booths during the various slots! Your donations will go a long way and make a positive difference to the youths! 🥰🥰

If you have any questions, feel free to PM ian (
) or laura (

text: Dear CAPTains,

As a College, it is important that we acknowledge the contribution of individuals who, through their commitment and dedication, have enriched community life in its broadest sense. 

The CAPT Awards are meant to recognize CAPTains who have been exceptional in demonstrating the College values of integrity, audacity, compassion and teachability (I-ACT), in any aspect of College life. This includes:

- Leadership and service
- Learning and intellectual growth
- Sports
- Arts and culture
- Community engagement            

All CAPTains are invited and encouraged to make one or more nominations for the various categories, and the awardees will be announced at the

There is no fixed number of awards; we hope to recognize as many deserving individuals as possible. Amongst the awardees under the College Award category, one or more outstanding individuals may also receive the CAPTain of the Year Award.

So, if you feel that a fellow CAPTain has inspired you and has gone the extra mile for the good of the College, help us recognize these individuals and celebrate their contributions as a community.

The nomination period
We look forward to receiving

Best regards,
College of Alice & Peter Tan

text:
Hi all, thank you for your support during the HH Dialogue Session. With this, we have now officially opened the voting period for Round 2. Please note that as we are in the cooling-off period, campaigning is strictly prohibited.

The voting form can be accessed via this

. Rest assured that your data and decision will remain confidential and only RAs will have access to the data collected.

Voting method: You can vote for one or none of the candidate(s).

IMPORTANT THINGS TO NOTE:
1. The minimum number of vote required is 60.
2. Candidates must have more than 40% confidence votes to be elected.
3. If neither candidate has more than 40% votes, we will open Round 3.

Please note that the election period begins on Wednesday (27 March) 0900 and ends on Thursday (28 March) 2100. No extension will be given after the form has closed. Results will be released on Friday.

If you have any questions, please feel free to reach out to the RAs

. Thank you!

- With 💙, Roc RAs

Hi guys! 👋

One of the community project under NUS Students' Community Service Club (NUSCSC), called Project We Are One (WAO) will be hosting Member of Parliament Mr Louis Ng for a dialogue on the Migrant Workers Community. 
The details are as follows:
📆: Friday, 5th April 2024
🕰️: 7pm to 9pm (Registration opens at 6.15pm)
📍: NUS S10 Multipurpose Room

Project WAO aims to raise awarness for the migrant workers' commiunity amongst NUS students through engagements with our migrant sisters and brothers. This is something similar to ACE Migrants!!

This is a good opportunity for all of yall to learn more about the migrant worker scene in Singapore 😊

Do drop me a text
if yall r interested by

text:
Hi ROCkers!!! Today is the start of ROC TOUCH!🧀

Details:
- Event will last for 3 days, from 2 Apr (Tues) to 4 Apr 2024 (Thurs)
- Effective timing of the event will be 10am - 10pm
- Anyone who have the ROCTouch (Clip) is considered infected with the disease until he/she passes it to someone else
- Objective: To pass the ROCTouch around using a special clip (plastic clothes peg)
- There will be 3 clips going around each day

Rules:
- To successfully pass on the ROCTouch,
   ~ kiap/attach the

💠 on someone’s belonging (e.g. person’s bag, or shirt/shorts that being worn)
   ~ Do

kiap on someone’s skin/hair🙅‍♀️
   ~ send a

in the house ‘chit chat’ channel showing the new victim with the kiapped blue clip as evidence.🤳
   ~ Every new ‘victim’ being kiapped by the clip must hold onto it for at least 🔟 minutes before passing it to the next victim.
- You

kiap someone who is already holding onto a clip.
- You can get infected again for an unlimited number of times.🦠🦠🦠
- You will only be considered ROCTouched if by 10pm, you are still holding onto a blue clip.😷
- ROCTouched individuals of the day will start the new round at 10am the next day
- People who r ROCTouched will have to complete a challenge at the end😈

MAY THE STRONGEST SURVIVE🦠🏃‍♂️🏃‍♀️

messages.text:
Hi ROCkers!!! Today is the start of ROC TOUCH!🧀

Details:
- Event will last for 3 days, from 2 Apr (Tues) to 4 Apr 2024 (Thurs)
- Effective timing of the event will be 10am - 10pm
- Anyone who have the ROCTouch (Clip) is considered infected with the disease until he/she passes it to someone else
- Objective: To pass the ROCTouch around using a special clip (plastic clothes peg with self adhesive tape on it)
- There will be 3 clips going around each day

Rules:
- To successfully pass on the ROCTouch,
   ~ kiap/attach the LIGHT BLUE CLIP/PINK💠 on someone’s belonging (e.g. person’s bag, or shirt/shorts that being worn)
   ~ Do NOT kiap on someone’s skin/hair🙅‍♀️
   ~ send a telebubble in the house ‘chit chat’ channel showing the new victim with the kiapped blue clip as evidence.🤳
   ~ Every new ‘victim’ being kiapped by the clip must hold onto it for at least 🔟 minutes before passing it to the next victim.
- You CANNOT kiap someone who is already holding onto a clip.
- You can get infected again for an unlimited number of times.🦠🦠🦠
- You will only be considered ROCTouched if by 10pm, you are still holding onto a clip.😷
- ROCTouched individuals of the day will start the new round at 10am the next day
- People who r ROCTouched will have to complete a challenge at the end😈

MAY THE STRONGEST SURVIVE🦠🏃‍♂️🏃‍♀️

messages.text:
Dear Esteemed ROC,

With a heavy heart and a humbled spirit, I pen this letter to express my profound apologies for the catastrophic defeat I suffered in the recent game of ROCTouch. The shame and embarrassment I have brought upon myself, my family, and the entire ROCTouch fraternity weigh heavily upon me, and I am acutely aware of the dishonor I have wrought upon all who hold this esteemed game dear.

My failure in the game of ROCTouch was not merely a loss; it was a crushing blow to my pride, my dignity, and my sense of self-worth. I recognize that in my defeat, I have tarnished the reputation of not only myself but also that of my family, who have stood by me in unwavering support throughout my ROCTouch journey.

The gravity of my failure is not lost on me. ROCTouch is not just a game; it is a symbol of skill, strategy, and sportsmanship. To falter in such a revered arena is to betray the very essence of what it means to be a ROCTouch player. My actions have besmirched the legacy of all those who have triumphed before me, and for that, I am truly sorry.

I pledge to you, my fellow ROCTouch enthusiasts, that this defeat will not define me. I will use it as fuel to propel myself to greater heights of excellence and mastery of the game in the future. I vow to redouble my efforts, to train harder, to strategize more diligently, and to approach each match with the utmost dedication and resolve.

Furthermore, I solemnly promise to uphold the values of integrity and honor that are synonymous with ROCTouch. I will conduct myself with grace and dignity both on and off the battlefield, striving always to be a beacon of sportsmanship and fair play.

In closing, I extend my deepest apologies to all those who were disappointed by my performance. I am profoundly sorry for the shame and disappointment I have caused, and I humbly ask for your forgiveness and understanding.

With utmost sincerity and contrition,

Jarod
Yeet

As we are approaching the end of the academic year (time flies! 🥹), let us come together one more time to celebrate our achievements and reminisce the ✨great memories ✨ we created over the past year 😊. Attire: Formal Wear

Please register via this form:
by

to register your attendance.

Note: There will be no dining hall services that day - those who are not able to attend the dinner are encouraged to sign up and select the 'take-out' option to ensure they have dinner.

- With 💙💚💛❤️🖤,
Special Events RAs

poll.question:
Do you think enough is being done to protect people accused of crime?
(if you are female, answer F, if male, answer M)

Should individuals who are accused of a crime be named in the news before being found guilty?
(if you are female, answer F, if male, answer M)

Before a conviction happens, should the name of the accused be released? 
(Petty crimes - theft, littering)

answers.text: Yes, people should know who committed it even if it is a petty crime.
No, a petty crime means that a conviction should happen before naming the accused.

poll.question:
Before a conviction happens, should the name of the accused be released? 
(Serious crimes - sexual assault, murder, kidnapping)

answers.text: Yes, a serious crime means that people should know who committed it.
No, a serious crime means that a conviction should happen before naming the accused.

text: HEY CAPTAINS 🔥🔥

thank you for the overwhelming sign-ups 🙏 

some of you may have some questions, so we have created some FAQs to answer your questions ⬇️⬇️⬇️
date:

time: 
(a)

text.text: where are the locations for CAPT-TU-CHAK?

text: Food booths -
Games -
Look out for the floorplan for the exact location of booths!

text.text: do i have to register? How will I redeem the food?

text: The registration is for redeeming the food, and SAC members will distribute the tickets to your doorstep! use the ticket to redeem your food - if you dont have a ticket, we cannot ensure that you can get food!

text.text: what if i don't want to eat everything on my ticket?

text: Do share with your friends, especially if they weren’t able to get a ticket from registration!
We have 2 time slots for food redemption! Each ticket entitles u to one serving of all 4 food items 🔥

text.text: what if I don't have a ticket? Or what if I lose mine?

text: Unfortunately there are only 250 tickets! We won’t be able to confirm that you can get food if you dont register 🙁

text.text: will I be able to get my food at my timeslot as long as I have the ticket?

text:
Yes! as long as you have your ticket you will be able to get your food and it is not first come first serve. So you won't need to come early to queue etc. 


But please be punctual to your slot - if you miss your time slot we cannot guarantee you will get your food!

Happy week 10!
Have a guitar you don't use anymore? Don't FRET😄 You can now DONATE them to the boys at Singapore Boys' Hostel by 🗓️

🔥

ACE Constellations aims to empower youths-at-risk through a guitar-teaching programme so that they may use music as a form of self-expression and emotional regulation. However, these boys do not have their own guitar... this donation drive will help to provide them with their very own guitar to practice and play whenever, wherever! Will this be the start of their singer-songwriter era? 🤔😎🤩

All types of guitars are welcomed, preferably in good condition! 🎸

If you are keen to give your guitars a new home, do contact Elijah (
) or Yien Ning (
) for the next step, by 25 April (Thursday)! Thank you for your donations❤️

messages.text:
Hello CAPTains, Farewell Dinner is happening TONIGHT! Here are some details pertaining tonight's event: 
 
🔖Registration starts at 530pm at MPSH. All attendees have to be seated in DH by 615pm so that we can start at 630pm promptly. Once registration is closed, you will have to wait outside DH before being allowed entry. 
 
💺When seated, please put your meal coupon on the table in front of you so that the servers can see your meal choice. 
 
⏰For latecomers: You may come to the table next to the stage inside DH for registration.  
 
🦥For those who opted for takeout: you may collect your food 👉🏼at 530pm👈🏼. Come to MPSH to collect your meal coupon, and then go to DH to collect your bento. If you are not around, you can ask your friend to collect on your behalf. Please bring your own container. 
 
That's all for now. For any live updates, look out for the messages sent by your RAs in your house chat. Thank you and see you later!  
 
💙💚💛❤️🖤, Special Events RA

messages.text:
Hi everyone! For this year’s farewell dinner, we have brought in a PHOTOBOOTH SERVICE🎪📸 for you to take photostrips with your friends! To ensure that everyone gets an opportunity to take some pictures, we will be enforcing the following rules: 

1. Please gather your entire group before joining the queue - no one will be admitted to the photobooth once the group has started queuing

2. You cannot queue for 2 groups at once (e.g. you cannot get 2 groups of friends to queue side-by-side) - please requeue if you want to take with multiple groups of friends

Failure to comply with the members of CSC/RAs who are managing the queues will result in you being unable to take your photos! Please cooperate with us so we can all make great memories at farewell dinner🫶

text:
As an initiative by CAPTains and for CAPTains, CAPT Support is a community passionate about mental well-being! We seek to promote awareness and understanding of mental health among CAPTains. We wish to create a safe space and a conducive environment in CAPT to scaffold CAPTains’ emotional well-being!  ❤️😀

If you share our goals and wish to shape the topics and conversations on mental health in CAPT, come and join our CAPT Support family! 💞🌱

Go to our

to find out more about our recruitment timeline, our direction, and what’s in it for EXCO members this AY! 🌟🆒

Please fill in the application form by Sunday, 26th May 2359! 

If you have any questions, feel free to contact Tiffany (
, Director), Zikri (
, Developmental Vice Director), Melissa (
, Internal Vice Director), and Yuxin (
, Outreach Vice Director)! 🫶🏻
